        <div class="snippet-answer">
          <p><strong>YouTube Ads</strong> are paid advertisements served through Google Ads on YouTube's platform and across Google Video Partner sites. Available formats include skippable in-stream ads (the ones you can skip after 5 seconds), non-skippable ads, 6-second bumper ads, and in-feed discovery ads. Campaigns leverage Google's full audience intelligence — demographics, intent signals, search history, and custom segments — making YouTube one of the most precisely targeted video advertising platforms available.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="term-meta-strip">
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Category</div>
            <div class="tms-value">Paid Advertising</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Also Called</div>
            <div class="tms-value">YouTube Video Ads</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Difficulty</div>
            <div class="tms-value">Intermediate</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Read Time</div>
            <div class="tms-value">9 min</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="lede-p">YouTube isn't just a video hosting platform — it's the second-largest search engine in the world, and its advertising platform sits directly on top of Google's audience data. That combination gives YouTube Ads a unique position: the reach of television, the targeting of digital, and the intent signals of search.</p>

        <h2 id="what-is">What are YouTube Ads?</h2>
        <p>YouTube Ads are purchased through Google Ads (formerly Google AdWords) and managed from the same campaign interface as search and display ads. They appear in three contexts:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>In-stream</strong> — before, during, or after YouTube videos</li>
          <li><strong>In-feed</strong> — in YouTube search results, the home feed, and the "up next" sidebar</li>
          <li><strong>Masthead</strong> — the hero placement on YouTube's homepage (reserved buy only)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>YouTube Ads are served by Google's auction system. Advertisers set targeting parameters, budgets, and bids — and Google's algorithms determine which ad shows to which viewer in which context, optimising for the advertiser's stated campaign goal (views, conversions, awareness).</p>

        <h2 id="formats">YouTube ad formats explained</h2>

        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Format</th><th>Length</th><th>Skippable</th><th>Pricing model</th><th>Best for</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="row-highlight">
                <td><strong>Skippable in-stream</strong></td>
                <td>12s minimum</td>
                <td>After 5s</td>
                <td>CPV (cost per view)</td>
                <td>Awareness + consideration</td>
              </tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Non-skippable in-stream</strong></td><td>15s or less</td><td>No</td><td>CPM</td><td>Guaranteed impressions</td></tr>
